<L>__{interior paul's kitchen. night}
<A>__{after dinner coffee for the adults. tatiana, thomas and fedens at the table. paul, in his usual position, at the head, listening, like solomon.}
<C>__{thomas}
<D>__{i've heard bad things, paul. my assistant says we should get out of rwanda.}
<C>__{fedens}
<D>__{why should we leave? i have a new job, things have never been better for us.}
<C>__{thomas}
<D>__{what good is it if we are murdered in our bed?}
<C>__{tatiana}
<D>__{your assistant, he is hutu?}
<C>__{thomas}
<D>__{yes, and he is in the hutu power militia.}
<C>__{carine}
<D>__{he wants your job.}
<C>__{thomas}
<D>__{no, he is a friend, but he tells me to listen to the radio. all day they talk about the great slaughter.}
<C>__{tatiana}
<D>__{that station is filth.}
<A>__{paul has listened, now he decides to speak.}
<C>__{paul}
<D>__{today i talked to my friend the american ambassador and colonel oliver of the united nations. they are preparing a banquet for the peace signing. the bbc are flying in their best reporters. the world is watching. there will be peace. don't listen to this man.}
<A>__{solomon has spoken. fedens smiles, tatiana rubs paul's arm.}
